MetLife Enters $3 Billion Credit Deal With Banks Including BofA

-- B y   B r o o k e   S u t h e r l a n d
-- 
2011-08-15T21:32:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-15/metlife-enters-3-billion-credit-deal-with-banks-including-bofa.html
MetLife Inc. (MET) , the biggest U.S. life
insurer, entered into a $3 billion credit agreement with lenders
including  Bank of America Corp. (BAC)   The insurer also reduced to $1 billion the amount available
on a three-year deal from last year that was originally for $3
billion, New York-based MetLife said today in a regulatory
filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brooke Sutherland in New York at 
 Bsutherland5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  